<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="727" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7289</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">T. K. Bewley</persName>, of
                                the British Supply Council in North America, to the Assistant
                                Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Acheson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-02">August 2,
                                1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Dean</hi>: This is to let you know that my
                            government has now proposed to the Chinese Government the appointment of
                            Mr. Hall Patch<note n="46" xml:id="d727fn1">Financial Adviser of the
                                British Embassy in China until 1939.</note> as British member of the
                            Stabilisation Board and that this proposal has been accepted by the
                            Chinese Government.</p>
                        <p>The appointment would be on a temporary basis and the more permanent
                            appointment would no doubt be the subject of discussion with Sir O. E.
                            Niemeyer.</p>
                        <p>I have also informed Mr. Cochran<note n="47" xml:id="d727fn2">H. Merle
                                Cochran, Technical Assistant to the Secretary of the
                                Treasury.</note> of the appointment.</p>
                        <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>T. K. <hi rend="smallcaps">Bewley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>